{
  "stem": "16930.1",
  "chunk_idx": 10,
  "model": "openai/gpt-oss-120b",
  "elapsed_s": 7.0,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 57,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "The troops weren't personally involved.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 57,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "The-- they weren't sort of like-- I don't think they were even antagonistic to us in any way.",
      "word_count": 18
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 57,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 6,
      "text": "I-- I-- all that thing in Germany, it grew.",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 57,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 7,
      "text": "I don't think essentially that the German people per se were much more evil any other people.",
      "word_count": 17
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 57,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 8,
      "text": "It's just when you have an evil ideology, like Nazism, fascist Nazism or Marxist atheist communism, it's that evil ideology which leads you to evil thoughts, which in turn lead you to evil action.",
      "word_count": 34
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 57,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 9,
      "text": "And you become evil in the process.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 57,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 10,
      "text": "But most of the troops there, they were sort of like an adventure, you know.",
      "word_count": 15
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 57,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 11,
      "text": "They're going to go to the front.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 57,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 12,
      "text": "They're going to a war.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 57,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 13,
      "text": "And you know, like young kid-- mostly young children, young, maybe 18, 19, or whatever their ages were.",
      "word_count": 18
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 57,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 14,
      "text": "And maybe even-- one of the-- I remember one of the group leaders, he was talking to them, you know.",
      "word_count": 20
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 57,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 15,
      "text": "And they were talking for-- back to him, you know, so that there was no-- we didn't see any-- I didn't feel any antagonism.",
      "word_count": 24
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 58,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "Well, maybe partially, you know.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 58,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "Going on a rail-- I'm going on a train and going on a ferry, you know.",
      "word_count": 16
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 58,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "And so in a sense, partially, yes.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 58,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "I wasn't scared.",
      "word_count": 3
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 58,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "There were all the other people there.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 58,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "And you know, it was sort of like-- it was not like people who went to concentration camps, who were on the way to be slaughtered.",
      "word_count": 26
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 58,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 6,
      "text": "There-- that was a different atmosphere.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 58,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 7,
      "text": "People knew they were on the way to be slaughtered.",
      "word_count": 10
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 58,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 8,
      "text": "The reactions of the people at the railroad stations was quite difference.",
      "word_count": 12
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 58,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 9,
      "text": "Even the people working the railroad, even the clerks in the offices of the various railroads knew they were going to slaughter.",
      "word_count": 22
    }
  ],
